Your Honor,

I stand before this court today, humbly pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. On the day in question, I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members who were visiting from out of town. Unfortunately, in my haste, I allowed my impatience to cloud my judgment, leading me to engage in aggressive driving behaviors, including exceeding the permitted speed limit and quickly responding to a text message.

I must acknowledge that I currently have three penalty points on my license for a previous speeding offense. However, I want to assure the court that this incident has served as a wake-up call for me.

In terms of my personal circumstances, I am 37 years old and, aside from the aforementioned infringements, possess an otherwise clean driving record. Furthermore, I strive to contribute positively to society through regular donations to the British Heart Foundation.

In light of this incident, I have already taken proactive steps to prevent any recurrence of such behavior. I have enrolled in defensive driving courses to enhance my knowledge and skills on the road. Additionally, I have made a sincere effort to educate myself and others about the potential risks associated with distracted driving.

I would like to clarify that my intention is not to downplay the seriousness of this offense. I regret my actions and understand the impact they could have had on myself and others on the road. I am fully aware of the dangers and risks associated with careless driving, and I take full responsibility for my actions.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I stand committed to accepting the consequences of my actions. It is my hope that the court takes into consideration my plea of guilty, which reflects my acknowledgement of wrongdoing. I assure you that I have learned a valuable and lasting lesson from this experience, and I am fully dedicated to becoming a safer and more responsible driver in the future.

Thank you for allowing me to address the court.

